            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/pyramidDescription"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="The Great Pyramid of Giza, also known as the Pyramid of Khufu or Cheops, is the oldest and largest of the three pyramids on the Giza Plateau near Cairo, Egypt. Constructed around 2560 BCE during the Fourth Dynasty of the Old Kingdom, it served as a tomb for Pharaoh Khufu and stands as one of humanityâ€™s most extraordinary achievements in architecture and engineering.
