\n\nInside, the pyramid houses a complex network of passageways and chambers, including the Kingâ€™s Chamber, Queenâ€™s Chamber, and the Grand Gallery. The original polished Tura limestone casing reflected sunlight, causing the structure to gleam brilliantly in the desertâ€”earning it the name 'Ikhet,' meaning 'Glorious Light.'
\n\nThe Great Pyramid forms part of a vast necropolis that includes smaller pyramids for queens, mortuary temples, and the Great Sphinx. It symbolizes the Egyptiansâ€™ deep religious beliefs in the afterlife and their desire to honor their pharaoh as a divine ruler. Today, it stands as the last surviving Wonder of the Ancient World, continuing to inspire awe as a timeless testament to human ingenuity, ambition, and devotion."
                android:textColor="#CFCFCF"
                android:textSize="15sp"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="4dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="20dp" />


            <TextView
